&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Title: Highly Specialist Occupational Therapist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: &lt;/strong&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 / 1.0wte. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone who is motivated to contribute, facilitate, design and lead service developments, innovations and audit within our critical care, surgery and cardiorespiratory services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our team supports the following areas:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A general 14 bedded critical care unit offering multi-organ support and post-operative care. We lead the rehabilitation of all patients and support the unit in meeting national standards for critical care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our surgical service includes patients requiring upper GI, colorectal and specialist vascular (including amputation) intervention. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder should have expertise in clinical reasoning, management of complex cases and advanced communication skills whilst working in a busy multi-disciplinary hospital environment. Senior experience working in respiratory, medicine, surgery and neuro is essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our team is friendly, supportive and pro-active providing opportunities for development of your clinical, leadership and management skills to progress in your career. We have an established formal supervision and appraisal process. There is robust in-house training programme for both junior and senior staff. The programmes allow you to improve your teaching skills and develop your knowledge and skills in our specialist area. Additionally we run monthly journal, quality governance and team meetings to evaluate our clinical practice and service ensuring that we are being responsive to the changing environment that we work in.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ashford and St Peter’s offers a seven day service across some specialities and you will be expected to support this on a rota system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a hospital hopper bus service which operates frequently throughout the day between Ashford and St Peter’s Hospital sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
